    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to both hand tools and large horse- or tractor-drawn vehicles that usually consist of a frame upon which is fastened shares, discs, or tines used for breaking up the surface of soil.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
